The NGO says the transport department has been following a reactive approach rather than a proactive one for years now. JOHANNESBURG - Road safety NGO South Africans Against Drunk Driving says that the Transport Department is to blame for the 5% increase in the road death toll. The department has confirmed that 1,714 people lost their lives over the holiday period.The NGO says that the Transport Department has been following a reactive approach rather than a proactive one for years now. The organisation's Caro Smit says law enforcement visibility is insufficient. They should be having traffic officers on duty 24 hours a day, seven days a week, 365 days a year and for those traffic officers to then enforce our very, very good laws. (Edited by Neo Koza)